---
description: WPF/XAML house conventions - apply when creating or editing XAML files.
globs: "**/*.xaml"
alwaysApply: false
---

When creating or editing XAML (`.xaml`) files, follow the house WPF conventions carried by
the `dotnet-wpf` skill installed under `.cursor/skills/`: strict MVVM, explicit binding
modes, and resource/theming conventions. Prefer these over ad-hoc style.

If the `dotnet-wpf` skill is not loaded, hold the line on the highest-value rules: no
code-behind logic (bindings and commands only), explicit `Mode=` on every `Binding` rather
than relying on the default, `DynamicResource` for theme-dependent values (not
`StaticResource`), and `x:Name` only when the element is referenced from code-behind or
another binding.

This is guidance, auto-attached whenever a `.xaml` file is in context (not a hard block).
